steps.prompt:
Draft a formal OSHA-compliant incident investigation report for the following construction site incident.

Project: {{project_name}} (Site: {{site_id}})
Incident date: {{incident_date}}
Incident type: {{incident_type}}
Injured count: {{injured_count}}
Severity classification: {{steps.triage-severity.output.severity_class}}
Regulatory obligations: {{steps.triage-severity.output.regulatory_obligations}}
OSHA notification submission: {{steps.submit-regulatory-notification.output}}
Initial incident report: {{steps.receive-incident-report.output}}
Investigation findings: {{steps.receive-investigation-findings.output}}

The report must include the following numbered sections:
1. Incident Summary — date, time, location, type, injured parties
2. Description of Events — chronological account leading to the incident
3. Root Cause Analysis — direct cause, contributing factors, root cause
4. Witness Statements Summary — anonymized if required
5. Regulatory Compliance — OSHA notification reference number, 300 log entry, state reporting status
6. Corrective and Preventive Actions (CAPA) — specific actions with responsible parties and due dates
7. Return-to-Work Plan — if applicable
8. Sign-off Section — fields for safety officer, project manager, and HR

Format as a formal professional document. Language must be factual, specific, and free of speculation.
